  "text": "The expression of the constitutively produced heat-shock chaperonins GroEL and DnaK appeared also to be upregulated under alkaline growth conditions. Under the steady-state conditions used in this study, the role of chaperonins is to modulate the folding of nascent polypeptides following translation as opposed to repairing or destroying denatured proteins during abrupt changes in growth conditions that induce a cellular stress response [CITATION_1] . The increased expression of GroELlike proteins, under conditions which mimic those in the periodontal pocket, is important as they have been reported to be immunodominant bacterial antigens that may play a role in pathogenesis by stimulating the host immune response (Skår et al., 2003) .",
